All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Board
Represents a board which is a matrix of board tiles.
BoardSpriteManager
This Class reads in and stores various resources we will use throughout the program.
BoardTile
Represents each tile that makes up the board One can get X,Y position and the type of a tile and whether a tile is open or not.
Button
This class is for creating the various JButtons that the game uses.
CharacterCommand
Interface class which contains a execute method to be implemented.
CharacterGraphic
Interface class which contains a getActiveImage() method to be implemented.
CollisionCheck
A utility class that checks collisions between entities, and other entities, and entities and the board.
DeepFryer
Represents a deep fryer which consists of x,y coordinates.
DifficultyScreen
This class creates and paints the difficulty select screen jpanel and its corresponding buttons.
Direction
Represents a direction which consists of UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT, STILL.
DoorKey
Represents a Door key which consists of x,y coordinates.
Entity
Abstract class that represents entity for all sprites (player character, fry cook, potato friend, key).
EntityFactory
 
FryCook
Represents a fry cook which consists of x,y coordinates and its left/right buffered images.
GameLoop
This class represents the game screen UI and the game loop which loops through the game logic at each tick to display and interpret all things that are needed to run the game.
GameState
Represents the game state such as difficulty, score, win/lose, # of keys collected, time, etc.
HelpScreen
Creates and paints the Help screen and its buttons.
HomeScreen
Creates and paints the Home screen and its buttons.
InputHandler
Handles the user's keyboard input.
Label
This class is for creating the various JLabels that the game uses.
LoseScreen
Creates and paints the Lose screen and its buttons.
Main
The main class of this game.
MapReader
This class reads txt files which contain the game's levels and returns them in a BoardTiles array
Movable
An entity that is able to move.
MoveDown
Moves the player down
MoveLeft
Moves the player left
MoveRight
Moves the player right
MoveUp
Moves the player up.
Music
Able to play music and stop the music.
NoMove
Don't move the player
PauseScreen
Creates and paints the Pause screen and its buttons.
PlayerCharacter
Represents the user's character.
PlayerTracker
This class represents the moving enemy's player tracker / search algorithm
PotatoFriend
Represents the bonus reward of the game
UICreator
Creates the GUI panels/objects of the game and initializes them.
WinScreen
Creates and paints the Winscreen and its buttons.
